{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_36","type":"agent_message","text":"The JUnit scanner itself is falling back to a plain filesystem walk of the explicit classpath root. That makes the remaining question very concrete: whether the native-image inputs already include the relevant `org_springframework/spring_test/*.class` files as resources, or whether we need to add those globs so the test’s root resolution can hit a real classpath directory instead of the executable path."}}
