{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_67","type":"agent_message","text":"The failure for `org.springframework:spring-test:7.0.0` was not caused by missing entries in [reachability-metadata.json](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/8258-764ac556/metadata/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/reachability-metadata.json). The native image built successfully; the breakage was in `TestClassScannerTest`, which fell back to scanning the native executable because `java.class.path` was not preserved for the native test process. I fixed that in [build.gradle](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/8258-764ac556/tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/build.gradle) by passing `-Djava.class.path=${sourceSets.test.runtimeClasspath.asPath}` to `nativeTest` and the GraalVM test binary runtime.\n\nVerification used the exact required GraalVM. `native-image --version` matched `25.0.3 2026-04-21 / Oracle GraalVM 25.1.0-dev+9.1`, and `env GRAALVM_HOME=... JAVA_HOME=... PATH=... ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.springframework:spring-test:7.0.0` now passes. After the patch, the native test log shows `TestClassScanner` scanning `build/classes/java/test`, and all 10 native tests succeed."}}
